 Knowing engineering ethics and societal responsibility,  emphasizing environmental protection and industrial safety
□ 終身學習成長之能力。
 Self-learning and growing
 

課程概述 Course Description
1.	Introduction
2.	Absorption of UV-Visible Light
3.	Characteristics of Fluorescence Emission
4.	Effects of Intermolecular Photophysical Processes on Fluorescence Emission
5.	Fluorescence Polarization. Emission Anisotropy
6.	Principles of Steady-State and Time-Resolved Fluorometric Techniques
7.	Effect of Polarity on Fluorescence Emission. Polarity Probes
8.	Microviscosity, Fluidity, Molecular Mobility. Emission by Means of Fluorescent Probes
9.	Resonance Energy Transfer and Its Applications
10.	Fluorescent Molecular Sensors of Ions and Molecules
11.	Advanced Techniques in Fluorescence Spectroscopy
    

課程學習目標 Course Objectives
1. 厚植專業知識與應用能力2. 強化獨立思考及創新研發能力教育學生認識工程倫理和社會責任，並拓展國際視野 

